cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ScribeBench: A Fidelity Benchmark for Clinical Documentation AI"
message: "If you use ScribeBench, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Napier
    given-names: Andrew
    name-suffix: MD
    affiliation: "Sayvant Health; Stanford University School of Medicine"
repository-code: "https://github.com/napiermd/scribe-bench"
abstract: >-
  ScribeBench evaluates clinical documentation AI on fidelity to the source
  encounter rather than structural completeness. It combines a six-dimension
  narrative-quality judge calibrated to blind physician preference, an
  adversarial fabrication judge that distinguishes registering delivered care
  from inventing what did not happen, and a deterministic leak scanner.
keywords:
  - clinical AI
  - ambient scribe
  - medical documentation
  - hallucination detection
  - LLM-as-judge
  - benchmark
license: MIT
version: 0.1.0
